  Metric: IteratorAgeMilliseconds
  Threshold: > 5000 (5 seconds)
  Action: SNS notification, Auto-scaling trigger
  
Dashboard:
  - IteratorAgeMilliseconds (trend)
  - Lambda Duration (processing time)
  - Lambda Throttles (capacity)
  - Producer vs Consumer rate (gap analysis)
```

**7. Example Troubleshooting:**

**Scenario: Iterator age = 30 seconds**
```
1. Check Lambda Duration: 2 seconds per batch (high!)
2. Check Lambda Throttles: Yes, being throttled
3. Check Reserved Concurrency: 10 (too low)
4. Check Producer Rate: 5,000 records/sec
5. Check Consumer Rate: 1,000 records/sec (can't keep up)

Solution:
- Remove reserved concurrency limit
- Increase Lambda memory (faster processing)
- Reduce batch size (lower latency)
- Add shards (more consumer capacity)
```

**Best Practices:**
- Monitor iterator age continuously
- Set up alerts for high lag
- Regular performance testing
- Capacity planning based on peak load
- Optimize before scaling (cost-effective)"

